WEBVTT

00:03.584 --> 00:05.316
So, Mike and Martina,

00:05.351 --> 00:07.686
let's talk about why you're
seeking therapy today.

00:07.721 --> 00:09.387
She made me.

00:11.592 --> 00:13.323
- What are you writing?
- Mike.

00:13.358 --> 00:14.625
He's just taking notes.

00:16.027 --> 00:18.963
He's writing about you now.

00:18.998 --> 00:20.731
You don't know that.

00:20.766 --> 00:22.265
Are you?

00:22.301 --> 00:23.801
Let's get back to why you're here.

00:23.836 --> 00:25.002
Yes.

00:25.037 --> 00:27.437
We're here about a
dilemma Mike's facing.

00:27.473 --> 00:30.473
It all began when I was
counseling a mother and daughter

00:30.508 --> 00:34.110
who were having some problems
since they moved in together.

00:34.145 --> 00:35.511
I just
can't control her.

00:35.546 --> 00:37.346
Coming in at all hours,

00:37.381 --> 00:39.582
drinking, loud music,

00:39.618 --> 00:41.618
an endless parade of men.

00:44.455 --> 00:47.889
I'm just having a little fun.

00:47.925 --> 00:50.826
Well, adult parents and
children living together again

00:50.861 --> 00:52.794
does present a lot of challenges.

00:52.830 --> 00:54.596
It certainly does.

00:54.632 --> 00:56.898
That stupid accent!

00:58.435 --> 00:59.534
It's not a choice.

00:59.569 --> 01:01.837
You married a British man
and raised me in London.

01:01.872 --> 01:05.105
Raised me in London.

01:05.141 --> 01:07.341
Who talks like that?

01:07.376 --> 01:09.977
Everyone in London!

01:10.013 --> 01:12.312
Can you even understand her?

01:14.117 --> 01:15.482
Mom, major emergency.

01:15.518 --> 01:16.450
Stella!

01:16.485 --> 01:17.818
I'm in session.

01:17.854 --> 01:20.354
You know I've said not to come
in when the door is closed.

01:20.389 --> 01:21.621
Yeah, but you also said

01:21.657 --> 01:23.289
you're sad you don't
have enough patients,

01:23.324 --> 01:27.160
so sometimes you just come
in here to cry, so...

01:27.195 --> 01:29.896
Stella, whatever it is,
we'll deal with it later.

01:29.931 --> 01:32.132
Oh, sorry about that.

01:32.167 --> 01:33.900
Now, let's get back...

01:33.935 --> 01:35.401
<i>Martina!</i>

01:35.436 --> 01:38.637
<i>I don't feel so good.</i>

01:38.673 --> 01:40.172
Whoa, whoa.

01:40.207 --> 01:42.607
Yes, I was a little under the weather,

01:42.643 --> 01:44.877
but that is not how it happened.

01:47.447 --> 01:49.281
Mike, what are you doing out of bed?

01:49.316 --> 01:51.349
You're deathly ill.

01:51.385 --> 01:52.751
Yes, I am,

01:52.787 --> 01:55.820
but that wood isn't gonna chop itself.

01:55.855 --> 01:57.989
That is not how it went.

01:58.024 --> 02:00.892
Although I would like
you to chop that wood.

02:00.927 --> 02:03.594
It's a lot of work.

02:03.629 --> 02:05.763
<i>Martina!</i>

02:05.799 --> 02:07.031
That's my husband.

02:07.067 --> 02:08.532
He's not feeling well,

02:08.568 --> 02:10.133
and you know how men get.

02:10.169 --> 02:11.502
She doesn't.

02:11.537 --> 02:12.936
Ugh.

02:12.971 --> 02:14.037
This again.

02:14.073 --> 02:15.806
She's a virgin.

02:17.076 --> 02:19.076
I am not a virgin.

02:19.111 --> 02:20.610
It can lapse!

02:20.645 --> 02:23.513
Like a driver's license.

02:23.548 --> 02:25.381
That's ridiculous.

02:25.417 --> 02:28.018
I was married up until ten years ago.

02:28.053 --> 02:30.786
I will admit it has been a while.

02:30.822 --> 02:34.190
There are cobwebs down there.

02:36.460 --> 02:38.728
Stop pushing me, Mother.

02:38.763 --> 02:40.730
I'll go out again when I'm ready.

02:40.765 --> 02:42.331
Look, we really don't mind

02:42.366 --> 02:43.899
if you need to tend to your family.

02:43.935 --> 02:45.967
Your daughter did say
it was an emergency.

02:46.002 --> 02:49.270
Well, thank you.

02:49.305 --> 02:52.140
I'm sure it's nothing, but
I will be right back.

02:54.677 --> 02:56.945
It must be nice to have a
daughter who needs you

02:56.980 --> 02:58.880
and wants your advice.

02:58.915 --> 03:01.482
You don't give me advice, just insults.

03:01.517 --> 03:03.183
I don't insult you.

03:03.219 --> 03:04.551
Just this morning you asked me

03:04.586 --> 03:08.355
which mortician died and
left me his clothes.

03:08.390 --> 03:12.092
A genuine question.

03:12.128 --> 03:15.028
All right, what's the big emergency?

03:15.064 --> 03:16.696
This is tough, Mom.

03:16.732 --> 03:18.565
Have you ever heard of
Lou Gehrig's disease?

03:18.600 --> 03:20.967
Yes. Oh, my God, Stella.

03:21.002 --> 03:24.771
Well, there's a play about
it, and I have an audition.

03:24.806 --> 03:26.906
But I told them I could
do accents, and I can't.

03:26.941 --> 03:28.440
Mom, help.

03:28.476 --> 03:29.842
It's the first day of my internship,

03:29.878 --> 03:30.943
and I'm freaking out.

03:30.979 --> 03:32.044
Which outfit says,

03:32.080 --> 03:33.146
"Take my seriously, damn it,

03:33.181 --> 03:35.214
but I'm a little fun."

03:35.250 --> 03:37.249
The left one.

03:37.284 --> 03:40.218
Oh, and you, Google "accents"
and do what they say,

03:40.254 --> 03:42.988
then Google "real problems"
and pay attention.

03:45.458 --> 03:50.195
Oh, I am so sorry for that interruption.

03:50.230 --> 03:51.496
Where's your mother?

03:51.531 --> 03:53.498
She went to help your husband.

03:53.533 --> 03:54.999
What?

03:59.172 --> 04:01.305
Is this helping you?

04:01.340 --> 04:02.940
I'm not sure.

04:02.975 --> 04:06.576
It's sure helping me.

04:06.612 --> 04:09.280
Sandy, what are you doing in here?

04:09.315 --> 04:13.316
She showed up and started
rubbing VapoRub on my chest.

04:13.351 --> 04:15.451
And...

04:15.486 --> 04:18.553
I just went with it.

04:18.589 --> 04:20.690
This is wrong. You can't be here.

04:20.725 --> 04:22.458
I'm your therapist.

04:22.493 --> 04:23.960
Oh, not anymore.

04:23.995 --> 04:26.662
This poor man needs me.

04:26.698 --> 04:28.297
That's my job.

04:28.332 --> 04:30.665
I think I can take care of my husband.

04:30.701 --> 04:32.801
So why aren't you feeding him?

04:32.837 --> 04:34.269
Feed a cold;

04:34.305 --> 04:35.670
starve a fever.

04:35.706 --> 04:37.372
I could eat.

04:38.608 --> 04:40.843
How do chocolate chip pancakes sound?

04:40.878 --> 04:43.912
Could you make the chocolate
chips into a smiley face?

04:43.948 --> 04:46.413
With a whipped cream beard.

04:46.449 --> 04:47.748
That sounds good.

04:47.783 --> 04:50.184
Can we keep her?

